To be honest, this was a hard one for after the first pick. As a Rakan main, it was relatively obvious that I would go with him. However, after that... it became kind of hard to imagine who I would be fine playing with only 6 champions. Soraka was my former main, so I suppose that one wasn't as hard -- Zyra is just... well, kinda there for when I need a poke-poke support.

Varus... well, he's what I would play in ADC role, I guess. I've always loved him, but I just don't play him because... well, not an ADC and Varus support doesn't work out that well (I've tried). Orianna is one of the first champions that drew me to League, despite never learning how to play her -- still think she's really cool though. Morgana is what I play midlane (because I need the W CS) and I enjoy her support as well. This was really hard and would probably change after Rakan, but this is what I got so far. lol

Braum's level 6 ganks are insane. His damage gets ramped up after either getting {{item:1416}}  OR {{item:1413}}  and {{item:3006}}  

Braum scales into the lategame as a tank that can easily do the broken strats that Sej and Zac used a while ago with {{item:3190}} and {{item:3193}} 

Braum can win most 1v1's if he uses Lethal tempo or Grasp of the undying
